DOC.TEXT:
The lead stories in major Taiwan dailies Tuesday are as follows:
@The Central Daily News:
Premier Vincent Siew nominates Minister-without-Portfolio Chao
Shou-po Taiwan governor.
@The China Times:
Central Bank of China announces cut in rediscount rate and interest rate on secured loan by 0.25 percent each.
@The United Daily News:
Central Bank of China again cuts rediscount and secured loan rates by 0.25 percent.
@The Liberty Times:
A total of 5,000 people were convicted of vote-buying for legislative candidate Wang Tao-fu three years ago, hitting new judicial record in Taiwan.
@The Independence Morning Post:
Newly-appointed Taiwan Governor Chao Shou-po is scheduled to take office on Dec. 21.
@The Commons Daily:
May newly-elected Taipei Mayor Ma Ying-jeou pave way for out-going Taiwan Governor James Soong for 2000 presidential elections?
@The China Post:
Taiwan trims interest rates after elections.
@The China News:
Central Bank drops interest rates.
CBC Chairman denies political motivations, affirms benefits to
local economy.

